Title: Self-Employment among Immigrants: A Last Resort?
Author-Name: Jensen, Kraen Blume
Author-Name: Ejrnaes, Mette
Author-Name: Nielsen, Helena Skyt
Author-Name: Würtz, Allan
Author-Email: awurtz@econ.au.dk
Author-WorkPlace-Name: Department of Economics Aarhus, Denmark
Author-WorkPlace-Postal: 8000 Aarhus C, Denmark
Author-WorkPlace-Fax: +45 86 13 63 34
Abstract: Based on unique register data of male immigrants in Denmark, we investigate whether self-
employment is used as a last resort. To identify self-employment as a last resort, we define
different types of immigrants as a function of transition probabilities between wage-employment,
non-employment and self-employment. The transition probabilities are estimated using discrete
competing risks models controlling for unobserved heterogeneity and duration dependence. We
find that for certain groups of immigrants, a large fraction can be characterized as using self-
employment as a last resort.
Classification-JEL: C23, C25, C41, J23
Keywords: discrete competing risks, duration, random effects, self-employment
